## React Hydration Issues and Solutions

### Critical Hydration Fixes for Mobile Success Pages

Mobile browsers are particularly sensitive to React hydration mismatches. The following issues were encountered and fixed:

#### Issue 1: Dynamic Debug Banners Causing Hydration Mismatch
**Problem**: Debug banners with dynamic server/client values (e.g., `{pi || 'N/A'}`) caused hydration failures.

**Solution**: Remove all debug banners from server components. Use logging instead:
```typescript
// ❌ BAD - Causes hydration mismatch
<div style={{ padding: '20px', background: 'yellow' }}>
  <p>PI: {pi || 'N/A'} | Session: {session_id || 'N/A'}</p>
</div>

// ✅ GOOD - Use console logging
console.log('[QR PAGE SERVER] Search params:', { pi, session_id });
```

#### Issue 2: Next.js Image Component Optimization Differences
**Problem**: Next.js `Image` component has different optimization behavior between SSR and client, causing hydration failures.

**Solution**: Use standard `<img>` tags in mobile success/loading pages:
```typescript
// ❌ BAD - Causes hydration mismatch
import Image from "next/image";
<Image src={heroImageUrl || "/default.jpg"} width={1200} height={400} />

// ✅ GOOD - Use standard img tag
<img
  src={heroImageUrl}
  alt="Event Hero"
  style={{ width: '100%', height: 'auto', objectFit: 'cover' }}
/>
```

#### Issue 3: dangerouslySetInnerHTML Style Injection
**Problem**: Injecting styles via `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` during hydration can cause timing mismatches.

**Solution**: Use inline styles or external CSS files:
```typescript
// ❌ BAD - Timing issues during hydration
<style dangerouslySetInnerHTML={{__html: `
  .hero-image { width: 100%; }
`}} />

// ✅ GOOD - Inline styles or Tailwind classes
<img className="w-full h-auto object-cover" />
```

#### Issue 4: Early Return Pattern Causing Different DOM
**Problem**: Returning different content on server vs client causes hydration mismatch.

**Solution**: Always render same base structure, use conditional rendering for progressive enhancement:
```typescript
// ❌ BAD - Different server/client DOM
const [mounted, setMounted] = useState(false);
useEffect(() => setMounted(true), []);

if (!mounted) {
  return <div>Loading...</div>; // Simple DOM on server
}
return <ComplexUI />; // Complex DOM on client

// ✅ GOOD - Same base structure, conditional content
return (
  <div className="min-h-screen bg-gray-100 flex flex-col">
    {mounted && <HeroSection />} {/* Progressive enhancement */}
    <LoadingContent /> {/* Always rendered */}
  </div>
);
```

#### Issue 5: Mount Guard Pattern for Client-Only Features
**Problem**: Client-only features (like hero image fetching) run on server causing errors.

**Solution**: Use mount guard with proper state initialization:
```typescript
const [mounted, setMounted] = useState(false);
const [heroImageUrl, setHeroImageUrl] = useState<string>("/images/default.jpeg"); // Default value

useEffect(() => {
  console.log('Component mounted on client');
  setMounted(true);
}, []);

useEffect(() => {
  // Client-only code runs ONLY after mount
  if (sessionId && mounted) {
    fetchHeroImage();
  }
}, [sessionId, mounted]);

// Render with conditional enhancement
return (
  <div>
    {mounted && <div>Client-only content</div>}
    <div>Always rendered content</div>
  </div>
);
```

#### Issue 6: Desktop Data Fetching Interfering with Mobile Redirect
**Problem**: Desktop transaction fetching useEffect runs simultaneously with mobile redirect logic, causing 404 errors and "Error: null" pages.

**Solution**: Use state coordination to prevent desktop fetch on mobile:
```typescript
// Track mobile detection state
const [isMobileDevice, setIsMobileDevice] = useState<boolean | null>(null);

// Mobile detection sets state immediately
useEffect(() => {
  const isMobile = /Android|iPhone|iPad/i.test(navigator.userAgent) ||
                   window.innerWidth <= 768;
  setIsMobileDevice(isMobile); // Prevents desktop fetch

  if (isMobile) {
    // Show brief success, then redirect
    setTimeout(() => router.replace(`/event/ticket-qr?pi=${pi}`), 2000);
  }
}, []);

// Desktop fetch waits for mobile detection and skips if mobile
useEffect(() => {
  if (isMobileDevice === null) return; // Wait for detection
  if (isMobileDevice === true) return; // Skip for mobile

  // Only desktop users reach here
  fetchTransactionData();
}, [session_id, isMobileDevice]); // Include isMobileDevice in deps
```

